radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases are clear; the liver enhances homogeneously; a 4-mm hypodensity in the caudate lobe and a tiny 3-mm hypodensity in segment II/III of the liver are noted; gallbladder unremarkable; portal vein patent; pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands normal; symmetric nephrogram in kidneys; no focal renal lesion; aorta normal; stomach and small bowel within normal limits; the appendix fluid-filled, measuring 10 mm, with mucosal enhancement; moderate pelvic free fluid present.
